parameters: \CL I feel like that beautiful chain is rejecting everything.

Bard: I'm glad it wasn't just my misunderstanding, there's
no doubt about it.
Bard: Is it okay for me to go ahead and slash?
Clea: Yes, please take care of me--

Actina's Priestess: The right to challenge to break the
chains... I certainly gave it as a reward for subduing the
demon bride Ancos.

Actina's Priestess: However! That is a matter only
concerning you all, that man over there should have no
involvement.

Imiselinus Priestess: This is a very important place for
both the Terios religion and the Atomis Temple.

Imiselinus Priestess: This is not a place where you can
easily invite others in.

Dayley's Priestess: It annoys me that I agree with these
people... but even I am against inviting outsiders.

Dayley's Priestess: For your information, I am still a
priestess.

Clea: It's difficult to explain, but this person should be
able to cut the chains of the full moon.

Bard: It seems like we're not welcome here, so let's go
soon.

Actina's Priestess: Please keep this place a secret and
refrain from speaking about it to others!

Actina's Priestess: Dragon Slayer, we are still in the
middle of our conversation, please wait--
Clea: The chains of the full moon have been severed!

Bard: I apologize for the vagueness, but there should be
something interesting deep inside here, so why don't you go
and check it out?

Bard: I think you guys can put up a good fight now, don't
you?

Actina's Priestess: W-Who exactly are you...? I would like
to hear if you are capable of cutting those chains...

Actina's Priestess: I-I apologize! I never expected that
you were truly the legendary... Ah, what should I even say?

Actina's Priestess: As the eldest daughter of the
priestess, I apologize...

Actina's Priestess: To think that the legendary hero is
still protecting the human world even now...

Imiserinos' Priestess: As the eldest daughter of the
priestess, I apologize...

Priestess of Deire: I've seen many self-proclaimed heroes
before... but to have the real deal right in front of me...
I can't believe it...

Priestess of Deire: W-What should I do... First, as the
eldest daughter of the priestess, I apologize...

Bard: Haha, don't worry, you girls look just like the real
goddesses.

Bard: Actina, the goddess who is aggressive and
inflexible.

Bard: Imiserinos, the goddess who is compassionate but
self-righteous.

Bard: Deire, the goddess who is moody and cunning, but
surprisingly level-headed.

Bard: Haha, even in front of me, you girls are always
competing to be the eldest daughter.

Actina's Priestess: I apologize for my unsightly
appearance. The fact that the hero has appeared before the
priestess once again...

Actina's Priestess: So, you're saying that you can receive
the divine oracle from the priestesses and save the people
in need!

Imiserinos' Priestess: I will immediately report this to
the High Priest!

Deire's Priestess: D-Does that mean the hero has abandoned
us?

Bard: Because both the demons and the goddesses have
disappeared, the protagonist of this world must be a human.

Bard: I only intervene in situations that cannot be
resolved by the priestesses' prepared insurance humans.

Bard: The priestesses should believe in the power of the
humans who defeated the dragons more than anyone else.
Bard: Well then, I'll go back to being a tone-deaf bard.
Actina's Priestess: Believe in the power of humans, huh...

Imiserinos' Priestess: Let's keep the fact that the hero
has appeared as our secret.

Deire's Priestess: I agree... As someone who has lived for
a long time, her words carry weight.

Actina's Priestess: I am grateful to have had the
opportunity to meet the Dragon Slayer, our esteemed hero.

Actina's Priestess: Please follow the words of the hero and
go to the other side of the chains.
Clea: Understood, I will go on the exploration.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Photizona Region/The Hero's
Ruins\c[0]

events.name: EV008アクティナの巫女からの依頼1-8

parameters:
Actina's Priestess: This is the place called the Hero's
Ruins, where only the heroes who have achieved great deeds
are allowed to enter.

Actina's Priestess: Can you see this? The entrance is
completely sealed by the chains of the full moon.
Clea: I wonder what could be beyond this?

Actina's Priestess: I don't know... It is said that only
the heroes can break these chains.

Actina's Priestess: This time, the reward is the
opportunity to challenge and break the chains that allow you
to come here freely.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
